lf in the subversive dismantling of the totalitarian linguistic regime and the foregrounding of previously marginalized subject positions. In Ukraine, work in these areas shows how the traumas of centuries of colonial oppression are being overcome through the carnivalesque decrowning of ideological dogmas and an affirmation of a new type of community, most recently demonstrated in the peaceful Orange Revolution of 2004. Mapping Postcommunist Cultures also critiques the neglect of the former communist world in current models of cultural globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLittérature russexHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aLittérature ukrainiennexHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aPostmodernism (Literature)xRussia (Federation). 0aPostmodernism (Literature)xUkraine. 0aPostmodernism (Literature)zRussia (Federation). 0aPostmodernism (Literature)zUkraine. 0aPostmodernisme (Littérature)xRussie. 0aPostmodernisme (Littérature)xUkrainexRussia (Federation)xUkraine. 0aRussian literaturexHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aRussian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aUkrainian literaturexHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aUkrainian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780773576506?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773576506423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773576506/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aG